It’s been quite a roller coaster ride, but hopefully I can schedule my procedure for late July this year. And hopefully, with this pandemic laying all of our healthcare wins bare, people in the future won’t be quoted $16k for a $5.5k procedure to line some exec’s pockets.

It cost her LESS THAN A THIRD of what I was quoted. On the one hand, I was absolutely relieved that I didn’t have to wait to have this procedure done, but on the other hand I was Furious, because the cost of healthcare is so grossly inflated in this country.

But when I mentioned this to a tech at my doctor’s office, she gave me information about a hospital in another country that does the same procedure for a lower cost. She herself had undergone the same procedure eight months ago, and she received amazing treatment.

So I looked into self-pay. I was quoted $16,800 for the surgery, the anesthesia, and the one night hospital stay. I resigned myself to the fact that it would take me years to save up that amount of money.
